    "relatedPatterns": "... we have one pattern, already, which brings out the useful character of gardens - both public and private ones - [[Fruit Trees (170)]]; we supplement this with a smaller, but as important aspect of the garden - one which every public and private garden should contain: enhance common land - [[Common Land (67)]] and private gardens - [[Half-Hidden Garden (111)]] with a patch where people can grow vegetables.\nTo fertilize the vegetables, use the natural compost which is generated by the house and the neighborhood - [[Compost (178)]]; and if possible, try to use water from the sinks and drains to irrigate the soil - [[Bathing Room (144)]] ...\n---\n[!cite]- Alexander, Christopher. _A Pattern Language: Towns, Buildings, Construction_. Oxford University Press, 1977, p. 818.",
